# ==========================================================================
# Apply template: git config --global commit.template ~/.config/.gittemplate
# Credit: this template's idea is copied from below projects.
# * https://chris.beams.io/posts/git-commit
# * https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#commit
# Check out there contributions for more details.
# ==========================================================================
# Title: Summary, imperative, start upper case, don't end with a period
#
# Commit message header example
# <type>(<scope>): <short summary>
#   │       │             │
#   │       │             └─⫸ Summary in present tense. Not capitalized. No period at the end.
#   │       │
#   │       └─⫸ Commit Scope: common|app-name|file-name|core|
#   │
#   └─⫸ Commit Type: build|ci|docs|feat|fix|perf|refactor|test
#
# A properly formed Git commit subject line should always be able to complete
# the following sentence: "If applied, this commit will <YOUR COMMIT>".
# For example: "If applied, this commit will refactor subsystem X for readability"
#
# <- No more than 50 chars. #50 chars is here: ->
# Write *TITLE* below:

# <Blank line between title and body>

# Body: Explain *what* and *why* (not *how*). Include task ID like
# Fixes #<issue number> or Closes #<pr number>
# <- Wrap at 72 chars. ############################## which is here: ->
# Write *BODY* below:

# <Blank line between body and footer>

# Footer: At the end: Include Co-authored-by for all contributors.
# Write *FOOTER* below:
avimitin <avimitin@gmail.com>
# <Trailing blank line>

